<TITLE> Wife putting man in dock over second marriage </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 4 (bdnews24.com)A Dhaka court Monday ordered former establishment joint secretary Md Asaduzzaman Junu to appear in the court on Sept 3 after hearing a case filed by his first wife accusing him of marrying again without her permission. Metropolitan magistrate AKM Emdadul Haque heard the case after Monju Ara Begum filed it with the Dhaka Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court Monday against Zaman and his second wife Begum Gul-e-Noor. The court, however, did not take Gul-e-Noor's 'offence' into cognisance. The case statement said the former joint secretary had married the complainant in 1972 and they had two sons. After some years, Zaman secretly married Gul-e-Noor and gradually shunned his first wife and sons. Monju Ara went back to her father's place with the sons. The eldest son lives in Australia, the mother said in her statement, and younger one is a Supreme Court lawyer now. She filed the case under Muslim Family Act 1961
